<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-22-0400 </DOCNO><TEXT>The booklet is intended for the general reader seeking answers to questionsabout radioactivity in everyday life. It presents information on radioactivityand its effects on man and on the environment. Each 'window' deals witha specific aspect, starting with the Chernobyl accident that releasedthe radioactivity cloud, the subsequent distribution and fallout of theradioactivity over Europe, and the resulting contamination of water,fish, soil, plant, animals and food, and man, as a consequence. Naturalradioactivity is also discussed. (HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>